== Ownership ==
The [[Government Pension Fund of Norway|Norwegian sovereign wealth fund]], which held over 5% of BlackRock from 2014 to 2016, has now significantly reduced its stake to less than 2%. In March 2018, [[PNC Financial Services|PNC]] was BlackRock's largest shareholder with 25% of all shares, but announced in May 2020 that it intended to sell all shares worth $17 billion.<ref>{{Cite news |title=BlackRock's largest shareholder sells 22% stake |url=https://www.ft.com/content/8813613e-c847-4d31-aa09-94e3268ea718 |access-date=2024-08-19 |newspaper=Financial Times|date=11 May 2020 |last1=Henderson |first1=Richard |last2=Noonan |first2=Laura |last3=Fontanella-Khan |first3=James }}</ref> Over 80% of BlackRock is owned by institutional investors. The 10 largest shareholders, as of June 30, 2024, are listed in the following table:<ref>{{Cite web |title=BlackRock, Inc. Common Stock (BLK) Institutional Holdings |url=https://www.nasdaq.com/de/market-activity/stocks/blk/institutional-holdings?page=1&rows_per_page=10 |work=Nasdaq  |language=de |access-date=November 12, 2024 }}</ref>
